dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v1.systemtemplate.fibex.fibex4flexray.flexraycommunication

Interface IAbsolutelyScheduledTiming

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity

    public interface IAbsolutelyScheduledTiming
extends IEntity
    IAbsolutelyScheduledTiming: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    Each frame in FlexRay is identified by its slot id and communication cycle. A description is provided by the usage of AbsolutelyScheduledTiming. In the static segment a frame can be sent multiple times within one communication cycle. For describing this case multiple AbsolutelyScheduledTimings have to be used. The main use case would be that a frame is sent twice within one communication cycle.

    • Method Detail

      • getSlotID

        long getSlotID()
        Query the value of the attribute SlotID.

        In the static part the SlotID defines the slot in which the frame is transmitted. The SlotID also determines, in combination with FlexrayCluster::numberOfStaticSlots, whether the frame is sent in static or dynamic segment. In the dynamic part, the slot id is equivalent to a priority. Lower dynamic slot ids are all sent until the end of the dynamic segment. Higher numbers, which were ignored that time, have to wait one cycle and then must try again. minValue: 1 maxValue: 2047

        Returns:
        The value or null
